  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Senior Electrochemical Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Roles and Responsibilities:</strong></p><p>Own electrode/catalyst development, cell design, and electrolyzer performance optimisation. Bridge labbreakthroughs to manufacturable solutions and collaborate on process and controls strategies for reliable commercial operation.</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Lead R&D on electrodes & catalysts: selection, synthesis, performance & durability testing.</li><li>Optimise operating parameters (current density, temperature, pressure) for efficiency & lifespan.</li><li>Design/optimise electrochemical cells; execute EIS/polarisation/aging tests; analyse degradation.</li><li>Collaborate on plant‑level design inputs: PFD/P&ID, instrumentation & controls, utilities.</li><li>Develop equipment/instrument lists and technical specifications; recommend suppliers.</li><li>Contribute to techno‑economic assessments (TEA) and design‑to‑cost trade‑offs.</li><li>Document methods, results, and acceptance criteria; contribute to IP disclosures.</li></ul><p><strong>Qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor’s/Master’s/PhD in Electrochemistry, Materials Science, or Chemical Engineering.</li><li>6–10+ years’ hands‑on electrochemical R&D (cells, electrodes, catalyst testing & analysis).</li><li>Experience translating lab results into pilot/manufacturing requirements.</li></ul><p></p>",
